6.  Consolidation of the capacity development program will need to go beyond information 
exchange  for  managers  and  training  of  technical  staff,  and  will  need  to  assess  which 
management  systems  need  to  be  introduced  or  enhanced.  This  could  include  financial 
management  software,  e-procurement,  geographical  information  systems,  land  valuation 
systems, human resources development measures, and management of the existing urban 
information system (known as “district data books”). Further capacity development requirements 
may  be  related  to  the  establishment  of  a  sub-national  investment  facility,  expected  to  be 
established under the decentralization and deconcentration 3-year implementation plan 2011–
2013. 

7.  The  team  leader  and  deputy  team  leader  will  be  responsible  for  the  day-to-day 
implementation  of  the  TA.  The  team  leader  and  deputy  team  leader  shall  be  primarily 
responsible for ensuring that the objectives and targets of the TA are achieved and compliant 
with  Asian  Development  Bank  (ADB)  policies  and  guidelines.  The  responsibilities  of  the 
consultants are as follows: 
(i)  manage and administer the day-to-day operations and implementation of the TA; 
(ii)  take the lead in networking activities with national and subnational organizations; 
(iii)  take the lead in policy dialogues related to the TA; 
(iv)  guide the activities of the training needs assessment and secure approval of the 
training course contents from the executing agency and ADB; 
(v)  plan, coordinate, manage, and evaluate training activities suitable for staff; 
(vi)  conduct periodic project reviews and evaluations, and assess the quality of all TA 
activities; 
(vii)  lead the formulation of the draft urban development strategy document; 
(viii)  provide  secretariat  services  and  technical  and  administrative  support  to  the 
interagency workshops and meetings related to the TA; 
(ix)  liaise with key development partners, national agencies, and other stakeholders; 
and 
(x)  prepare for ADB the necessary briefings and progress reports. 

B.  Specific Terms of Reference 

8.  Team leader—urban management and finance expert (national, 22 person-months, 
full-time). The team leader will 
(i)  monitor overall performance of the TA; 
(ii)  lead the preparation of pilot capacity development and scaling-up activities; 
(iii)  lead the preparation of knowledge products; 
(iv)  lead the institutionalization of the program; 
(v)  review internal and external quality audit reports and recommend any necessary 
responses, and review all other reports as appropriate; and 
(vi)  lead coordination with the executing agency and major stakeholders. 

9.  Advisor—urban  development  and  management  expert  (international,  7 person-
months, intermittent). The advisor will  
(i)  assist the team leader and guide the consultant team in conducting a training 
needs assessment and preparing curricula; 
(ii)  assist the core team on implementation of management workshops and technical 
courses;

