(iii)  assist the team leader on quality control of documents; 
(iv)  assist the team leader on how to scale up the capacity development program;  
(v)  assist the team leader on the preparation of the draft urban development strategy 
document (i.e., the urban code); and 
(vi)  assist  in  the  preparation  of  an  institutionalization  strategy  for  capacity 
development. 

10.  Deputy team leader—urban planner (national, 12 person-months, intermittent). The 
deputy team leader will 
(i)  assist the team leader in guiding the consultant team; 
(ii)  assist the team leader in the preparation of pilot capacity development activities; 
(iii)  assist the team leader in the preparation of knowledge products; 
(iv)  assist the team leader in the institutionalization of the program; 
(v)  review internal and external quality audit reports and recommend any necessary 
responses, and review all other reports as appropriate; and 
(vi)  assist the team leader in communicating with the executing agency and major 
stakeholders. 

11.  Procurement  specialist  (national,  6  person-months,  intermittent).  The  procurement 
specialist  will  assist  the  team  leader  and  deputy  team  leader  on  the  procurement-related 
aspects of the following core tasks: 
(i)  training needs assessment; 
(ii)  curricula preparation; 
(iii)  implementation of management workshops and technical courses; 
(iv)  preparation of consolidated training materials; 
(v)  quality control; and 
(vi)  institutionalization of the program. 

12.  Social  safeguards  specialist  (national,  6  person-months,  intermittent).  The  social 
safeguards specialist will assist the team leader and deputy team leader on matters relating to 
resettlement  and  land  acquisition, indigenous peoples,  and  gender  action  planning  for  the 
following core tasks: 
(i)  training needs assessment; 
(ii)  curricula preparation; 
(iii)  implementation of management workshops and technical courses; 
(iv)  preparation of consolidated training materials; 
(v)  quality control; and 
(vi)  institutionalization of the program. 

13.  Environment  specialist  (national,  6  person-months,  intermittent).  The  environment 
specialist will assist the team leader and deputy team leader specifically on matters relating to 
the initial environmental examination, environmental analysis, and climate change adaptation for 
the following core tasks: 
(i)  training needs assessment; 
(ii)  curricula preparation; 
(iii)  implementation of management workshops and technical courses; 
(iv)  preparation of consolidated training materials; 
(v)  quality control; and 
(vi)  institutionalization of the program.

