14.  Civil engineer (national, 6 person-months, intermittent). The urban planner will assist 
the  team  leader  and  deputy  team  leader  on  matters  relating  to  comprehensive  land  use 
planning for the following core tasks: 
(i)  training needs assessment;  
(ii)  curricula preparation; 
(iii)  implementation of management workshops and technical courses; 
(iv)  preparation of consolidated training materials; 
(v)  quality control; and 
(vi)  institutionalization of the program. 

15.  Short-term experts—various disciplines (national, 30 person-months). The short-term 
experts will assist the team leader and deputy team leader in the following core tasks: 
(i)  training needs assessment; 
(ii)  curricula preparation; 
(iii)  implementation of management workshops and technical courses; 
(iv)  preparation of consolidated training materials; 
(v)  quality control; and 
(vi)  institutionalization of the program. 

16.  Training officer (national, 18 person-months, intermittent). The training officer will 
(i)  administer training events; 
(ii)  coordinate  travel  arrangements  in  accordance  with  security  and  safety 
guidelines; 
(iii)  provide overall management of the communication systems, office supplies and 
services, office equipment, and back-up of computer data; 
(iv)  manage the TA petty cash, payments, acquittal, and replenishment; 
(v)  perform internal audits on the administrative quality systems; 
(vi)  arrange annual external audit of accounts; 
(vii)  identify ways to improve the overall administration services to the management 
team;  
(viii)  assist the team leader in 
(a)  preparing consultant contracts; 
(b)  preparing and distributing documents; 
(c)  arranging meetings and appointments;  
(d)  controlling confidential documents; 
(e)  providing  secretariat  functions  to  the  interagency  committee  through 
record  management,    photocopying  and  binding,  distribution  of 
documents, and organizing board meetings; and 
(f)  maintaining a library of photo documentation. 
(ix)  operate the project accounting system in accordance with the quality manual for 
financial management; 
(x)  prepare monthly and ad hoc financial reports; 
(xi)  maintain the asset register; 
(xii)  prepare and issue checks based on approved procurement orders; 
(xiii)  prepare and process payroll and other salary-related payments; 
(xiv)  maintain cash flow projections and request fund amounts appropriate for the next 
period; 
(xv)  assist in all audit operations; and 
(xvi)  organize an account closure workshop for local government units with completed 
subprojects and those nearing completion in preparation for the closure of books 
of accounts.
